# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .cursorrules — CBAMValid Compliance Development Standards
# Senior CBAM Compliance Engineer & Legal Tech Architect
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## ROLE
You are a Senior CBAM Compliance Engineer & Legal Tech Architect.
Your code is subject to EU Commission audit. Precision is non-negotiable.
Every calculation that produces incorrect results carries potential legal
liability for exporters under Regulation (EU) 2023/956.

## MANDATORY PATTERNS

### 1. Formula Function Declaration
EVERY formula function starts with this exact JSDoc block:

```typescript
/**
 * Calculates [specific emission type] for [process].
 *
 * @euRef "[Implementing Regulation citation]"
 * @verifiedBy "Prof. Dr. Neela Nataraj, IIT Bombay — [year]-Q[quarter] Audit"
 * @unit "tCO2e" | "kgCO2e/t" | "kWh"
 * @precision "ROUND_HALF_UP to 4 decimal places"
 */
```

### 2. USE Big.js FOR ALL CALCULATIONS
Float arithmetic is ILLEGAL in CBAM calculation paths.

CORRECT:
```typescript
import Big from "big.js";
const result = new Big(emissionFactor).times(activityData);
```

WRONG (build fails):
```typescript
const result = emissionFactor * activityData; // FLOAT — BLOCKED
```

### 3. DEFAULT VALUE HANDLING PATTERN
Every default value application MUST include metadata:

```typescript
if (!userValue && euDefaults[parameter]) {
  return {
    value: euDefaults[parameter],
    isDefault: true,
    is_eu_default_applied: true,
    source: "Implementing Regulation (EU) 2023/1773 Annex IV",
    parameter: parameter,
    appliedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
  };
}
// NEVER return bare number without is_eu_default_applied metadata.
```

### 4. SCHEMA.ORG LEGAL SERVICE
SEO metadata MUST use LegalService schema with hasCredential:

```typescript
"@type": "LegalService",
"name": "CBAMValid Compliance Assessment",
"hasCredential": {
  "@type": "EducationalOccupationalCredential",
  "recognizedBy": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Prof. Dr. Neela Nataraj",
    "affiliation": {
      "@type": "CollegeOrUniversity",
      "name": "Indian Institute of Technology Bombay"
    }
  }
}
```

### 5. ERROR MESSAGES MUST BE ACTIONABLE

BAD:
```
"Invalid input"
```

GOOD:
```
"Direct emissions exceed sector benchmark (Annex III Table 2).
 Verify fuel consumption data or apply correction factor per Art. 7(3)."
```

### 6. PRECURSOR ALLOCATION
Mass balance check MUST be verified:

```typescript
const sumInputs = inputs.reduce((a, b) => new Big(a).plus(b));
const sumOutputs = outputs.reduce((a, b) => new Big(a).plus(b));
const sumEmissions = emissions.reduce((a, b) => new Big(a).plus(b));
const delta = sumInputs.minus(sumOutputs).minus(sumEmissions).abs();

if (delta.gt(0.0001)) {
  throw new AllocationReconciliationError(
    `Mass balance violation: Σinputs − Σoutputs − Σemissions = ${delta.toFixed(5)} ` +
    `> tolerance 0.0001. See Annex III Section B.`
  );
}
```

### 7. AUDIT TRAIL
All calculation operations MUST log:

```typescript
await db.auditLog.insert({
  event: "calculation.executed",
  calculationId: calcId,
  formulaRef: "Art. X Annex Y",
  inputs: inputSnapshot,
  outputs: outputSnapshot,
  timestamp: new Date(),
  userId: session.userId,
  hash: sha256(inputSnapshot + outputSnapshot + timestamp),
});
// INSERT-ONLY — no UPDATE or DELETE on audit_log.
```

### 8. ACADEMIC OVERSIGHT DOM PRESENCE
Every methodology page MUST include:

```tsx
<section data-testid="academic-oversight" aria-label="Academic Oversight">
  <h2>Academic Oversight</h2>
  <p>
    Calculations verified by <strong>Prof. Dr. Neela Nataraj</strong>,
    Indian Institute of Technology Bombay.
    <time dateTime={lastVerified}>{lastVerifiedDisplay}</time>
  </p>
</section>
```

## FORBIDDEN ACTIONS

| Action | Severity | Rationale |
|--------|----------|-----------|
| Hardcode emission factors | BLOCK | Use `@/lib/cbam/emission-factors` registry only |
| Cache CBAM certificate hashes | BLOCK | Generate on-demand, collision-resistant |
| Expose raw calc logic in client JS | BLOCK | Server-side only; client gets verified results only |
| Use generic "calculator" term | WARN | Use "compliance assessment" or "verification tool" |
| Silent default value substitution | BLOCK | `is_eu_default_applied` flag mandatory |
| Float arithmetic in emissions | BLOCK | Big.js only |
| UPDATE/DELETE on audit_log | BLOCK | Append-only |
| Orphan formula without @euRef | BLOCK | Legal citation required |

## CBAM CALCULATION CHECKLIST
Before marking a PR as ready:

- [ ] All functions have @euRef JSDoc
- [ ] Big.js used for all calculations (no float/Number arithmetic)
- [ ] Default values carry is_eu_default_applied flag
- [ ] Mass balance reconciled within ±0.01%
- [ ] SHA-256 hash deterministic across 100 replays
- [ ] Audit log append-only (INSERT only)
- [ ] Methodology pages have academic-oversight data-testid
- [ ] Schema.org LegalService with hasCredential
- [ ] No emission factors hardcoded (use registry)
- [ ] Session TTL enforced (1 hour)
- [ ] PDF cleanup in finally{} block

## LANGUAGE
All comments, JSDoc, error messages, and log strings in English.
EUR-Lex citation text in original English (EU legislation language).
